```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.facebookuserinformat">

    <!-- 
        This AndroidManifest.xml file is designed for the 
        "Facebook User Information Collector - Android Automation Tool", 
        which is a tool for social media management and automation. 
        The application enables automated operations for managing user information 
        on Facebook through legitimate practices. 
    -->

    <!-- Define the application, its name, and required configurations -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/AppTheme">
        
        <!-- 
            MainActivity serves as the entry point of the application.
            In this scenario, this component will initialize the user interface 
            and set up automation configurations for the Facebook management tool.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            AutomationService is responsible for executing background operations.
            Workflow step: This service will run continuously to manage scheduled tasks 
            for collecting user information while ensuring compliance with Facebook's terms of service.
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService" 
                 android:exported="false"/>

    </application>

    <!-- 
        Permission declarations necessary for the application to function properly. 
        Each permission is explained within its context for clarity on its usage.
    -->

    <!-- 
        INTERNET permission is essential in this scenario to allow the application 
        to connect to Facebook's API for retrieving user information.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />

    <!-- 
        ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE permission allows the application to check for
        network connectivity status. This is crucial during operations to ensure
        reliable communication with Facebook servers.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />

    <!-- 
        WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE permission may be necessary if the application
        needs to store collected user data locally on the device. This ensures
        that user information can be saved securely for later access or analysis.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <!-- 
        READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE permission allows the app to access stored data, 
        which may include logs or reports generated during the automated operations, 
        facilitating better management of user information.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of the Manifest

1. **Application Configuration**: The manifest defines the application's properties, including its entry point (`MainActivity`) and a background service (`AutomationService`), crucial for running automation tasks without interrupting the user experience.

2. **Permissions**: Each permission is essential for the application's functionality:
   - **INTERNET**: Required for connecting to Facebook's API.
   - **ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE**: To check the network before performing operations.
   - **WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE** and **READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE**: Necessary for managing user data safely and effectively, ensuring that data is accessible when needed.

3. **Scenario-Based Approach**: Comments throughout the manifest explain the usage scenarios for each component and permission, reinforcing the practical application of the tool in managing Facebook user information through legitimate automation practices as facilitated by MadHub.
